        "text": "<https:\/\/whalebird.social> is probably most similar to Slack in terms of UI, but like all Mastodon clients, <https:\/\/github.com\/h3poteto\/whalebird-desktop\/issues\/4504#issuecomment-2314518471|topic-oriented content discovery> is what's needed.\n\nBTW, this ability in the fediverse to mix and match your preferred client app with your preferred server, though the opposite of \"situated software\", still brings a smile to my face. It takes \"To each his own\" to its extreme. Is there a name for this kind of software? :slightly_smiling_face:",
